AÂ total of 236,864 internally displaced persons have returned to their homes in Benue, Taraba and Nasarawa States. Force Commander of Operation Whirl Stroke (OPWS), Major-General, Adeyemi Yekini, disclosed this to journalists in Makurdi yesterday. He took journalists around parts of Keana town and Giza in Keana Local Government Area of Nasarawa State. He said 201, 854 of the returnee IDPs were from Benue, 15,000 from Nasarawa and 10,000 from Taraba. Meanwhile, districts heads of devastated communities in Guma Local Government Area of Benue State have appealed to the Federal Government to rebuild homes in their domains so that their people taking refuge at various IDP camps could return home. The monarchs made the appeal separately in their speeches on Monday when they led newsmen in on an assessment tour to hitherto troubled areas of the LGA. The traditional heads of Mbabai, Mbadwen, Umenger, and Yogbo districts all in Guma LGA, expressed gratitude to the military for restoring normalcy in their crisis-torn communities occasioned by suspected herders attack. 120 births recorded in Benue IDP camps Special armed forces did not kill herdsmen, cows as alleged by Miyetti Allah - DHQ Military gives militia December to vacate Benue, Taraba, Nasarawa